    </table>

    <h2>1. Reach-In Commercial Refrigerators</h2>
    <p>Reach-in refrigerators are the standard for commercial kitchen ingredient storage. They're upright, with doors on the front, and maintain temperatures between 2°C and 8°C — the safe zone for chilled food storage as required by FSSAI.</p>

    <h3>Single-Door Reach-In (150–300 Litres)</h3>
    <p>The entry-level commercial refrigerator. Suitable for small bakeries, cloud kitchens, and cafés with limited storage needs. At ₹25,000–₹65,000, these are affordable but have limited capacity. Indian brands like Blue Star, Voltas, and Haier make commercial single-door models. Imported brands like Hoshizaki and Williams command higher prices but offer better energy efficiency and build quality.</p>

    <h3>Double-Door Reach-In (400–600 Litres)</h3>
    <p>The most popular commercial refrigerator size for Indian food businesses. Provides adequate storage for most medium-sized kitchens. Two independent doors allow quick access to specific sections without cooling loss. Prices: ₹55,000 – ₹1,20,000 for Indian brands; ₹1,00,000 – ₹1,80,000 for imported brands.</p>

    <h3>Triple-Door Reach-In (700–900 Litres)</h3>
    <p>For kitchens with high ingredient turnover. Three sections can be organised by ingredient type (dairy, produce, prepared foods). Prices: ₹1,00,000 – ₹2,00,000.</p>

    <h2>2. Under-Counter Refrigerators</h2>
    <p>Under-counter refrigerators fit beneath prep tables and keep frequently-used ingredients close to the work area. They're 85–90 cm tall and typically 60–120 cm wide. Ideal for pastry stations, sandwich prep areas, and bar setups. Prices: ₹20,000 – ₹55,000.</p>
    <p>The convenience factor makes under-counter fridges worth the investment — having ingredients at hand reduces the number of trips to the main refrigerator and improves kitchen efficiency.</p>

    <h2>3. Commercial Display Refrigerators</h2>
    <p>Display refrigerators are glass-fronted units designed to show your products to customers while keeping them chilled. They're essential for bakeries displaying cakes, pastries, and desserts, and for cafés showing cold beverages and grab-and-go items.</p>

    <h3>Upright Glass-Door Display Fridge</h3>
    <p>Tall units with one or more glass doors. Maximum visibility, often with LED internal lighting to make products look appealing. Prices: ₹35,000 – ₹1,50,000 depending on size.</p>

    <h3>Counter-Top Display Fridge</h3>
    <p>Smaller display units that sit on a counter or display stand. Ideal for bakeries with limited floor space. Prices: ₹20,000 – ₹80,000.</p>

    <h3>Cake Display Counter</h3>
    <p>Curved or flat-glass display counter specifically designed for cakes and pastries. Often with LED lighting and temperature control to 4–8°C. These are a significant investment (₹60,000 – ₹2,50,000) but dramatically increase impulse purchases in a bakery setting. Read our detailed guide: <a href="/blog/bakery-display-counter">Bakery Display Counter Price & Options India</a>.</p>

    <h2>4. Commercial Freezers</h2>
    <h3>Chest Freezers</h3>
    <p>Chest freezers are energy-efficient (cold air doesn't spill out when opened) and offer large storage capacity at low cost. The downside is that organisation is difficult — items at the bottom are hard to access. Best for bulk storage of items you don't access frequently. Prices: ₹20,000 – ₹90,000 for 200–700 litre commercial models.</p>

    <h3>Upright Commercial Freezers</h3>
    <p>More organised than chest freezers, with shelves for easy access. More expensive and slightly less energy-efficient, but much more practical for a working kitchen. Prices: ₹35,000 – ₹1,50,000.</p>

    <h2>5. Blast Chillers and Shock Freezers</h2>
    <p>A blast chiller rapidly reduces food temperature from +70°C to +3°C in under 90 minutes. This is critical for HACCP compliance and extends product shelf life significantly. For bakeries using the bake-off model (bake products partially, blast chill, then finish-bake to order), a blast chiller is essential equipment.</p>
    <p>Blast chiller prices in India: ₹1,20,000 – ₹9,00,000 depending on capacity (5-tray to 20-tray models). European brands like Icematic, Irinox, and Electrolux are the gold standard. Indian-assembled blast chillers are available at lower prices but with variable quality.</p>

    <h2>6. Walk-In Cold Rooms</h2>
    <p>When your cold storage needs exceed what reach-in units can handle, a walk-in cold room is the answer. Walk-ins are modular, assembled on-site from insulated panels (typically 80–100mm polyurethane foam panels), and can be any size. They can be refrigerators (maintaining 0–4°C) or freezers (maintaining -18 to -22°C).</p>

    <h3>Walk-In Cold Room Cost Factors</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Size</strong>: The biggest cost driver. Larger rooms cost more in panels, refrigeration unit, and installation</li>
      <li><strong>Temperature</strong>: Freezer rooms cost 30–50% more than refrigerator rooms due to heavier insulation and more powerful refrigeration units</li>
      <li><strong>Location</strong>: Installation in an existing space is cheaper than building a new structure</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigeration unit</strong>: Brands like Danfoss, Tecumseh, and Bitzer are reliable choices for the refrigeration unit</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Walk-in cold room prices in India: ₹2,50,000 – ₹20,00,000+ depending on size and specifications.</p>

    <h2>Commercial Refrigerator Brands in India</h2>
    <h3>Indian Brands</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Blue Star</strong>: Good quality, strong service network, competitive pricing. Popular for reach-in refrigerators</li>
      <li><strong>Voltas</strong>: Tata group brand. Reliable and well-serviced across India</li>
      <li><strong>Haier Commercial</strong>: Affordable range, widely available, decent quality for the price</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Imported Brands</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hoshizaki</strong> (Japan): Premium build quality, exceptional energy efficiency, high price. Used in 5-star hotels and upscale restaurants</li>
      <li><strong>Williams</strong> (UK): Professional grade refrigeration. Popular in hotel kitchens and high-end restaurants</li>
      <li><strong>True Manufacturing</strong> (US): Heavy-duty reach-in refrigerators with excellent longevity. Available through importers</li>
      <li><strong>Electrolux Professional</strong>: Good range including blast chillers and display cases</li>
    </ul>

